{"word":"ὑποστρέφω","slug":"ὑποστρέφω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ὑποστρέφω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὑπό\">ὑπό</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:στρέφω\">στρέφω</a></el>] ‘go back to a position’, <b>return <a href='B:480 14:40'>Mk 14:40</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a>; <b><a href='B:490 1:56'>Lk 1:56</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in Lk and Ac; in <b><a href='B:680 2:21'>2 Pt 2:21</a></b> the referent for the position to which one returns is implied and precedes the intervening experience of ‘the way of righteousness.’ <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ὑποστολή\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ὑποστρωννύω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}